        <hr>

        <section id="dashboard-overview">
            <h2>1. Dashboard Overview</h2>
            <p>The Dashboard provides a consolidated, real-time summary of the user's interaction with the Vidyari platform. Key metrics (e.g., total uploads, pending payments, recent activity) are displayed immediately upon login.</p>

            <h3>1.1 User Roles and Access</h3>
            <p>The Dashboard interface dynamically adapts based on the user's primary role (e.g., **Creator** vs. **General User**), prioritizing relevant tools like earnings reports for Creators and download history for General Users.</p>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="content-management">
            <h2>2. Content Management Module</h2>
            <p>This module provides comprehensive tools for Creators to manage their submitted digital assets.</p>

            <h3>2.1 Manage Uploads</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Status Tracking:** Displays the current state of all uploaded files (e.g., **Draft, Pending Review, Live, Rejected**).</li>
                <li>**Editing:** Allows modification of metadata (Title, Description, Tags, Price) for Live and Draft content.</li>
                <li>**Withdrawal/Deletion:** Provides options to temporarily hide (Withdraw) or permanently remove (Delete) content from the platform.</li>
                <li>**Re-upload/Versioning:** Supports updating existing files without creating a new content entry, preserving existing analytics.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Coupon Code Management</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Code Generation:** Tools to create new promotional coupon codes (fixed amount or percentage discount).</li>
                <li>**Configuration:** Setting parameters such as **Expiry Date, Usage Limit (Total/Per User),** and target content ID.</li>
                <li>**Performance:** Tracking the redemption rate and revenue generated by specific coupon campaigns.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="analytics-reporting">
            <h2>3. Analytics and Reporting</h2>
            <p>This section offers quantitative data on content performance, enabling creators to optimize their offerings and pricing strategies.</p>

            <h3>3.1 Key Metrics Displayed</h3>
            <ul>
               <li>Total Income: Total income you Earned from Your Digital Products</li>
               <li>Graphical view of Your income</li>
               <li>See Transactions Done on  Your products with payment id , data, total amount, discount, status</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3.2 Reporting Tools</h3>
            <p>Users can generate customizable reports spanning specific timeframes (e.g., last 7 days, monthly, annual) in common formats like **CSV** for external analysis.</p>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="earnings-payouts">
            <h2>4. Earnings and Payouts</h2>
            <p>This module handles all financial aspects related to content monetization, transaction tracking, and payment disbursement.</p>

            <h3>4.1 Earnings Summary</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Gross Revenue:** Total sales generated by content.</li>
                <li>**Platform Fee Deduction:** Transparent display of the service fee applied to gross revenue.</li>
                <li>**Net Earnings:** Final amount credited to the user's account balance.</li>
                <li>**Pending Balance:** Earnings secured but awaiting the final payment settlement period.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.2 Payout Configuration</h3>
            <p>Users must configure and verify their preferred payout method (e.g., bank transfer, digital wallet). Payouts are processed upon reaching the minimum threshold balance on the **1st and 15th of every month**.</p>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="account-settings">
            <h2>5. Account and Security Settings</h2>
            <p>This area provides administrative controls for the user's profile and security.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>**Profile Management:** Update display name, profile picture, bio, and associated external links (e.g., social media).</li>
                <li>**Password Update:** Functionality for changing the primary email address and resetting the login password.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="purchase-history">
            <h2>6. Purchase and Download History</h2>
            <p>This module provides a complete record of content acquired by the user.</p>

            <h3>6.1 Download History (Free Content)</h3>
            <p>A chronological list of all free assets accessed, including the date of download and file size. Files can typically be **re-downloaded** from this list.</p>

            <h3>6.2 Purchase History (Paid Content)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Transaction Record:** Details of paid transactions, including purchase date, final price paid, and any applied coupon.</li>
                <li>**Invoice Generation:** Users can generate official invoices or receipts for tax and record-keeping purposes.</li>
                <li>**Access Link:** Permanent access to the purchased content download link.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

